eNCA speaks to the President's spokesperson Vincent Magwenya. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has denied hiding the theft of around $4-million from his Limpopo farm. Former State Security Head Arthur Fraser laid a criminal complaint against the Ramaphosa. WATCH: Fraser vs Ramaphosa | Unpacking the criminal complaint laid against president Fraser alleges suspects colluding with Ramaphosa's domestic worker stole the money in 2020. The money was the proceeds of game that had been sold. Fraser claims the suspects were kidnapped and interrogated on the President's property and later bribed for their silence. He accuses Ramaphosa of concealing the crime from both the police and SARS. Ramaphosa has denied this. He says he was at an African Union Summit at the time of the robbery and reported the matter to the head of the Presidential Protection Unit. Ramaphosa says he's ready to co-operate with any investigation into the matter.  PRESIDENCY RESPONDS TO CLAIMS BY MR ARTHUR FRASER
The Presidency has been made aware through a media statement that Mr Arthur Fraser has laid a complaint with the South African Police Service against President @CyrilRamaphosa.